shared_text:
Sonoma County Office of Education
August 24 at 2:05 PM ·

The pandemic, wildfires, social justice movement, and other current events have heightened the need to be sensitive to the effect these events can have on children. Thankfully, any parent, teacher, or adult who works with children can be a source of healing when armed with the right tools.

SCOE's mental health team has curated a range of resources to help children cope with trauma and deal with their stress in positive ways, as well as resources for how to identify and help a child in crisis.

Access these resources at scoe.org/traumahelp.

Dear Students and Parents of SVUSD,

Zoom is currently experiencing technical difficulties today on a broad scale beyond SVUSD. We appreciate your patience as teachers, and the District, try to troubleshoot. Families may check their Google Classroom, student email, and REMIND text notifications for communications from teachers. Thank you for your patience as we work to find solutions!

Estimados estudiantes y padres de SVUSD,

Zoom actualmente está experimentando dificultades técnicas hoy en día a gran escala más allá del SVUSD. Agradecemos su paciencia mientras los profesores intentan solucionar problemas. Las familias pueden consultar su Google Classroom, el correo electrónico de los estudiantes y las notificaciones de texto REMIND para las comunicaciones de los maestros. ¡Gracias por su paciencia mientras trabajamos para encontrar soluciones!

Due to recent power outages at the Sonoma Valley Unified District Offices and power shutoffs in Sonoma, CA, tonight's regularly scheduled board meeting is continued to a date and time to be announced. Given the outbreak of three significant wildfires in Sonoma County, CA, and in Napa, California, and the current state of the COVID-19 pandemic, coupled with technical difficulties of proceeding, we believe the continuation furthers the safety of our staff and our community, which is always our paramount concern.

Be safe and be well.

Sonoma Valley Community Health Center
August 13 at 6:12 PM ·

EN VEZ DE "Feria de Regreso a Clase"

Estimada Comunidad,

Como muchos de ustedes se han preguntado, este año no pudimos hacer la "Feria de Regreso a Clase" . Sin embargo, sabemos lo importnate que son los utiles para los estudiantes en nuestra comunidad. En vez este año donamos $4000 a Sonoma Valley Unified School District para que ellos pudieran comprar kits y dar a los estudaintes. Agradecmos a WestAmerica Bank porque parte de estos fondos, $1500 fueron donados por ellos. Agradecemos a nuestros socios comunitarios que con los que llevado acabo los eventos en el pasado y esperamos regresar con el evento en 2021.

FISH, La Luz Center Sonoma Valley Hospital 4Cs of Sonoma County Valley of the Moon Lions Sonoma Sheriffs Office

shared_text:
Sonoma Valley Community Health Center
August 13 at 6:04 PM ·

IN LIEU OF "Back to School Health Fair"

Dear Community-
As many of you may have asked yourselves, this year we were unable to host "Back to School Health Fair". Nonetheless, we know how important school supplies are for children in our community and in lieu this year we donated $4000 to Sonoma Valley Unified School District so they could provide school supply kits for students. We are especially grateful to our local WestAmerica who put $1500 of the funds donated. We are especially grateful to the partners who have made this possible in the past and we hope to resume in 2021.

FISH, La Luz Center Sonoma Valley Hospital 4Cs of Sonoma County Valley of the Moon Lions Sonoma Sheriffs Office

post_text:
Sonoma County Office of Education (SCOE) is now offering a series of parent support during distance learning!

¡La Oficina de Educación del Condado de Sonoma (SCOE) ahora ofrece una serie de apoyo para los padres durante el aprendizaje a distancia!
shared_text:
Sonoma County Office of Education
August 17 at 3:56 PM ·

Save the date for the first event in a series of parent support forums hosted by the Sonoma County Office of Education to support families in distance learning. A panel of SCOE technology and educational support experts will be on hand to provide tips, resources, and answer questions from the community.

Topics will include guidance on technology, how to set up a positive learning environment, and student/family rights and expectations under distance learning.

Upon registration, you will have the chance to submit questions in advance. This forum is meant to provide general information support to families.

Specific questions including district-specific policy should be directed to your school or district.

Register here: https://bit.ly/ParentSupportSCOE

Sonoma Family Life Magazine Sonoma County Library

SVUSD is very excited to offer a new independent study program (K-12) called Valley Home Academy. The goal of the Independent Study Program (IS/VHA) is to provide an individualized educational plan for pupils whose needs may best be met through study outside the regular classroom setting. This is a voluntary program and both the district and families must agree for the student placement for participation.

Applications can be found on the District Webpage and applications are due Friday, August 7th!

Sonoma County Office of Education
July 20 at 2:35 PM ·

Save the Date: Community Update on Sonoma County Schools

Save the date for a community update where SCOE will provide information to students, families, staff, and the general public on school reopening. We will discuss Governor Newsom's latest mandate for schools, including distance learning, under what conditions schools can reopen for in-person instruction, mask/social distancing requirements, and more.

Share your general questions in advance at communications@scoe.org and we will address as many as we can during the presentation. Specific questions about grading, distance learning curriculum, and more should be directed to your local school district.

Event Details:

text:
Sonoma County Office of Education
July 20 at 2:35 PM ·

Save the Date: Community Update on Sonoma County Schools

Save the date for a community update where SCOE will provide information to students, families, staff, and the general public on school reopening. We will discuss Governor Newsom's latest mandate for schools, including distance learning, under what conditions schools can reopen for in-person instruction, mask/social distancing requirements, and more.

Share your general questions in advance at communications@scoe.org and we will address as many as we can during the presentation. Specific questions about grading, distance learning curriculum, and more should be directed to your local school district.

Event Details:
Wednesday, July 22
12:00pm

post_text:
Interested in Independent Study?

The District is beginning to develop an Independent Study program. This program will be for families who choose to have their students stay home and do much of the teaching at home. While still being developed, this is for independent learners and is generally an hour a week with a teacher. Expect enrollment information by early July. If you are interested, please email Ksherman@sonomaschools.org so we can be sure you get specific information.

También estamos comenzando a desarrollar un programa de estudio independiente. Este programa será para las familias que eligen que sus estudiantes se queden en casa y harán la mayor parte de la enseñanza en casa. Si bien aún se está desarrollando, este programa es para estudiantes que aprenden de forma independiente y generalmente incluye una hora a la semana con un maestro. Esperen información de las inscripciones a principios de julio. Si están interesados, envíen un correo electrónico a Ksherman@sonomaschools.org para que podamos estar seguros de obtener información específica.

Participants will be able to access the camp from a mobile device, tablet, or computer with an internet connection.

post_text:
PLEASE BE AWARE: It has come to our attention that parents of SVUSD students may have received calls from persons claiming to be an SVUSD employee asking for personal information, including Social Security Numbers (SSN). Never provide personal information, especially Social Security Numbers, to anyone you do not personally know or who calls claiming to be an employee of SVUSD. SVUSD employees are not allowed to ask for SSNs, and any request is an attempt to steal personal information.

POR FAVOR, TENGA EN CUENTA: Nos ha llamado la atención que los padres de estudiantes de SVUSD pueden haber recibido llamadas de personas que dicen ser un empleado de SVUSD pidiendo información personal, incluidos los Números de Seguro Social (SSN). Nunca proporcione información personal, especialmente Números de Seguro Social, a nadie que no conozca personalmente o que llame para reclamar ser un empleado de SVUSD. Los empleados de SVUSD no pueden solicitar SSN, y cualquier solicitud es un intento de robo de información personal.

Children who are not currently members can attend free of charge provided that a parent or legal guardian completes the membership registration form so the Club has emergency contact info. Read more at: http://campaign.r20.constantcontact.com/render?preview=true&m=1109991760516&ca=3ce67efb-61b3-478d-b165-0232c7c46860&id=preview

Hello, Sonoma Valley Unified School District Families-
PG&E has announced they will be shutting off power to the City of Sonoma beginning at midnight tonight. All SVUSD schools will be closed Wednesday, 10/9 - Friday, 10/11. Please see the attached letter from Superintendent Shiels.

Hola, familias del Distrito Escolar Unificado del Valle de Sonoma-
PG&E ha anunciado que estarán cerrando el suministro de energía eléctrica en la Ciudad de Sonoma a partir de la media noche esta noche. Todas las escuelas de SVUSD estarán cerradas desde el miércoles, 9 de octubre hasta el viernes, 11 de octubre. Por favor vean la carta adjunta de la Superintendente Shiels.
